<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued June 30 at 2:45PM CDT until June 30 at 3:30PM CDT by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 330 PM CDT
FOR NORTHEASTERN RANDALL AND SOUTHEASTERN POTTER COUNTIES...
At 244 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 4 miles south of
Amarillo, moving north at 20 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible. Hail
damage to vehicles is expected.
Locations impacted include...
Amarillo, Canyon, Lake Tanglewood, Mescalero Park and Timbercreek
Canyon.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
